akas: Lab Rats: Bionic Island USA (fourth season title)
akas from release info: Lab Rats: Bionic Island USA (fourth season title)

1.title: Bionic Rebellion: Part 1
1.plot: With stolen explosives, Sebastian readies his revenge against the Davenports for the death of Victor Krane.

2.title: Bionic Rebellion: Part 2
2.plot: Chase, Adam, Bree and Leo learn that a friend has formed an evil rebellion to exact revenge, leading to a bionic battle of good versus evil.

3.title: Left Behind
3.plot: While Adam, Bree and Chase fail to return Spin and Bob from an unauthorized field trip, Donald gets stuck wearing something he shouldn't.

4.title: Under Siege
4.plot: When Perry's nasty niece Kerry comes to the island school for a stay, things start getting destroyed. Kerry's the prime suspect, but bionic evidence leads Chase to believe not all of Sebastian's rebels were rounded up.

5.title: Bionic Dog
5.plot: A remnant of Victor Krane's evil comes to the island academy in the form of Douglas' long-lost bionic dog Otis, bringing allergies to Chase, obedience to Adam, and a mission to kill.

6.title: Mission Mania
6.plot: Leo's effort to draw public attention for himself winds up flooding the school phone lines with non-emergency calls.

7.title: Simulation Manipulation
7.plot: Adam and Chase each lead their own student groups against each other in a series of simulated exercises that will evaluate both student and mentor performances.

8.title: Forbidden Hero
8.plot: As Leo recuperates from a minor injury, Tasha learns she's been deceived about his level of participation in the hero missions.

9.title: Spider Island
9.plot: For fun on a day off, Douglas and Chase bring a long-extinct prehistoric sea-spider back to life, which soon puts one Academy member's life in immediate danger and imperils the rest.

10.title: Spike vs. Spikette
10.plot: Bree and Chase discover that a female bionic student has a commando app like Chase. After she starts terrorizing the academy, they activate Spike to subdue her.

11.title: Space Elevator
11.plot: Donald's top scientist, Dr. Ryan, arrives at the academy to test his latest advance in space technology - Chase's Space Elevator.

12.title: Bionic Action Heroes: Part 1
12.plot: Douglas reveals that a former colleague is a movie director who wants to make a movie based on Adam, Bree, and Chase; when the director shows up to the academy with her actor, Troy West, for research, her evil agenda begins to unfold.

13.title: Bionic Action Heroes: Part 2
13.plot: Having won an initial battle against Giselle and Troy, the bionic team scrambles to find the abducted Chase before Giselle has time to cut him open for his bionic chip.

14.title: One of Us
14.plot: S-1's return makes the team aware of a doomsday virus embedded in Krane's ex-soldiers that leaves all bionic teens with only ten hours to live before exploding as human bombs.

15.title: Lab Rats vs. Mighty Med: Part 1
15.plot: Chase and Donald create a new, groundbreaking energy source and unveil it to the world. Meanwhile, Kaz and Oliver infiltrate the academy in hopes of Kaz finally obtaining powers.

16.title: Bob Zombie
16.plot: Douglas develops a new piece of technology replicating Chase's bionic intelligence and gives it to some of the other academy students, including Bob.

17.title: Human Eddy
17.plot: Donald gives Eddy, the smart home system, a synthetic human body, and Human Eddy quickly becomes a model employee working alongside Perry.

18.title: The Curse of the Screaming Skull
18.plot: Perry brings back a skull from a neighboring island and everyone is convinced that it's cursed.

19.title: Lab Rats: On the Edge, Part 1
19.plot: While trying to prove his worth before his bionic step-siblings, Leo permanently injures a teammate, all because the U.S. President overlooked him for an upcoming team award.

20.title: Lab Rats: On the Edge, Part 2
20.plot: Racked with guilt over blinding a teammate, Leo moves back to Mission Creek, but his self-exile ends when his family finds itself in extreme danger.

21.title: Ultimate Tailgate Challenge
21.plot: To score a ticket to an alma mater collegiate football game (against Tasha's alma mater team), Perry uses her car as a cooking implement.

22.title: And Then There Were Four
22.plot: Adam, Bree and Chase are surprised when they find out they have another bionic sibling who was adopted and had a normal life.

23.title: Space Colony: Part 1
23.plot: Donald takes everyone for a visit to "Davenportia," the first human space colony located on a remote planet in another galaxy.

24.title: Space Colony: Part 2
24.plot: Krane's evil cohort, Dr. Gao, reveals their plan to wipe out and replace Earth's population with a bionic civilization.

25.title: The Vanishing: Part 1
25.plot: The academy students begin to vanish after receiving an operating system upgrade. The Davenport group puts their lives at risk when they face off against the vanished students' captors - a nefarious duo they recognize from their past.

26.title: The Vanishing: Part 2
26.plot: Giselle forces Douglas and Donald to watch their bionic creations and academy students suffer before killing them all, but she fails to regard Leo.

1.title: Crush, Chop, and Burn: Part 1
1.plot: When his mom marries a geeky billionaire inventor, Leo discovers that he has three bionically enhanced teenagers living in the basement of his new home.

2.title: Crush, Chop, and Burn: Part 2
2.plot: When Donald arranges to send his three bionically enhanced teenagers to a remote facility, they take measures to remain and keep their new best friend Leo company.

3.title: Commando App
3.plot: Donald permits his bionic teens to attend high school, but getting on the bad side of school football bullies triggers Chase's macho alter-ego to emerge and put them in their place.

4.title: Leo's Jam
4.plot: A dance is coming up, and Adam and Chase strive to help Leo look heroic to catch the interest of the girl of his dreams.

5.title: Rats on a Train
5.plot: A runaway train presents the bionic superteens their first practical test.

6.title: Smart and Smarter
6.plot: A less-than-perfect grade prompts super-smart Chase to run for Student of the Semester to prove his superiority to all.

7.title: Exoskeleton vs. Grandma
7.plot: Rose, Tasha's criticizing mother, comes to visit, and Tasha hopes there'll be no suspicious activities or behaviors in the house to set her off.

8.title: Bionic Birthday Fail
8.plot: The Davenport teens decide to throw Leo a surprise birthday bash. Surprisingly, they forget to invite Leo to it.

9.title: Death Spiral Smackdown
9.plot: Principal Perry ups the ante for the school's annual athletic challenge and Leo tries to use one of his bionic buddies to gain an advantage.

10.title: Can I Borrow the Helicopter?
10.plot: Growing pains hit the Davenport household over issues of trust, privacy and living together as roommates.

11.title: Back from the Future
11.plot: A visitor from the future comes to the secret laboratory - Leo.

12.title: Chip Switch
12.plot: After exchanging their super-abilities with one another, the superteens accidentally trap Leo in the school elevator with Principal Perry.

13.title: Drone Alone
13.plot: When Donald and Tasha leave for a trip to Australia they leave Leo & the bionic kids home alone. Leo accidentally activates one of Mr. Davenport's devices which causes the bionic kids to glitch.

14.title: Chore Wars
14.plot: The bionic kids learn about chores, allowances, money and greed and conduct a yard sale that goes wrong.

15.title: Dude, Where's My Lab?
15.plot: When Tasha complains about Donald's addiction to technology, Donald proposes a tech-free beach day. Unfortunately, an incoming solar flare requires the bionic trio to remain in the RV/mobile lab instead of enjoying the beach.

16.title: Air Leo
16.plot: While Leo aims to take on the 5-time school one-on-one basketball champ with some technological help, Adam auditions for an open spot on the cheerleading team against Bree.

17.title: Night of the Living Virus
17.plot: With intent to speed up a download, Leo eliminates a firewall that allows a virus to enter Donald's software and turn Eddy evil.

18.title: Mission Invisible
18.plot: The bionic teens are in danger of exposure when Principal Perry's newly installed security cameras capture superpowers in action.

19.title: Concert in a Can
19.plot: Jealousy arises when new student Marcus bonds quickly with Adam and Chase and the three form a band together, but Leo's antipathy turns out to be more justifiable than first thought.

20.title: Mission: Space
20.plot: Marcus wheedles himself into staying with the Davenports over the same weekend that an emergency necessitates Donald sending the superteens into space.

1.title: Speed Trapped
1.plot: Unbeknownst to the rest, Marcus programs Donald's self-driving car to speed Leo to his death, and Eddy contends with Tasha over anniversaries, wedding versus activation.

2.title: Spy Fly
2.plot: Without permission, Leo uses Donald's robot fly to secretly film Bree, but an accident unleashes a swarm of them upon the school that goes berserk, attacking the student body.

3.title: Missin' the Mission
3.plot: Leo takes on a challenge to prove his worth.

4.title: Quarantined
4.plot: Davenport discovers that Bree was exposed to a toxic chemical.

5.title: Robot Fight Club
5.plot: Donald vengefully enters a robot battling competition against Chase and Leo. Meanwhile Adam must date Bree's friend Caitlin to keep Caitlin quiet after witnessing Bree's bionic powers.

6.title: Bro Down
6.plot: Chase outsmarts Adam with a prank that hurts his aura of invincibility, leaving Adam abnormally aware and fearful of all potential hazards.

7.title: The Rats Strike Back
7.plot: The Lab Rats go on strike with Leo, their negotiator, up against the supreme rule of Donald Davenport.

8.title: Parallel Universe
8.plot: Leo is inadvertently transported to a parellel universe!

9.title: Spike's Got Talent
9.plot: Being overlooked brings out the worst in Chase and Bree in and around a school talent show.

10.title: Leo vs. Evil
10.plot: Leo follows Marcus to a secret lair.

11.title: Hole in One
11.plot: Covering up their damage to Donald's recently purchased high-end painting, the teens may end up putting Donald behind bars for forgery.

12.title: Trucked Out
12.plot: Davenport sets out to buy newly-licensed driver Adam a new, safe vehicle, and Tasha crimps Leo's style by running for PTA president.

13.title: The Bionic 500
13.plot: Donald and his obnoxious new neighbor settle their differences in a high-stakes stock car race.

14.title: Bionic Showdown: Part 1
14.plot: Douglas is revealed as Marcus' master.

15.title: Bionic Showdown: Part 2
15.plot: With Adam, Bree, Chase and Donald captured and stripped of bionic powers, only Leo and Eddy are left to pull off a rescue.

16.title: Memory Wipe
16.plot: Leo uses a memory-erasure device on Donald and accidentally wipes out 24 years.

17.title: Avalanche!
17.plot: Heedless of Donald's warning, Chase braves the arctic to retrieve rare minerals, only to become trapped in an avalanche and rescued unexpectedly by a familiar yet unwelcome face.

18.title: Adam Up
18.plot: Adam and Leo use a cloning device to create another Adam.

19.title: Llama Drama
19.plot: Adam and Chase are assigned to guard the school's mascot dingo costume from a rival school, at which they fail.

20.title: The Haunting of Mission Creek High
20.plot: Trent the bully is tormenting Leo again but Leo's found his weakness - he's afraid of ghosts.

21.title: Perry 2.0
21.plot: In technologically upgrading Mission Creek High, Donald eagerly gives Perry a robotic version of herself to help patrol the students, which leaves Leo and Chase taking heat from the student body for it.

22.title: My Little Brother
22.plot: Chase inadvertently shrinks Adam down to two inches!

23.title: Prank You Very Much
23.plot: Bree is tired of being the target of the boys pranks and partners with Donald for payback.

24.title: Twas the Mission Before Christmas
24.plot: It's Christmas Eve and the Lab Rats have to go on a rescue mission to Donald's secret facility in the frozen tundra.

25.title: Trent Gets Schooled
25.plot: Trent demands that Leo and Chase help him study for a science test.

26.title: No Going Back
26.plot: Donald is under attack by a hacker that has not only left Davenport Industries in ruins but has stolen his entire fortune.

1.title: Sink or Swim: Part 1
1.plot: As Leo, Tasha and Donald deal with eviction, Adam, Bree and Chase lie low aboard a cargo freighter as stowaways, but a crisis challenges the teens' resolve to stay off the grid.

2.title: Sink or Swim: Part 2
2.plot: Donald, Tasha and Leo must try to reach the human sides of the bionic teens when Douglas uses the Triton App in their bionic implants to set them against their own family.

3.title: The Jet-Wing
3.plot: Donald tries to raise money for a new lab by attempting a death-defying stunt where he flies over Mission Creek on rocket-propelled wings.

4.title: Mission: Mission Creek High
4.plot: Now that Principal Perry knows the Lab Rats' bionic secret, she pesters the team to take her on a mission.

5.title: Zip It
5.plot: Bree gets a job at a tech store, excited to have something to do not involving her family or bionics - until Chase also gets a job there. Meanwhile, Adam, Leo and Donald set up advanced zip lines around the house instead of doing chores.

6.title: Not So Smart Phone
6.plot: Chase panics. His new cell phone (with a recording of Chase and Adam using bionics) gets lost among others on sale at Tech Town. Meanwhile, Leo finds it is in his best interest to stop Principal Perry from retiring.

7.title: Scramble the Orbs
7.plot: Leo invents Attack Orbs, floating robotic bodyguards that will attack any threat coming within five feet of him.

8.title: Principal from Another Planet
8.plot: Principal Perry invades the Daveport mansion during a lunar eclipse to declare an alien invasion at hand. Turns out, she might be correct.

9.title: Taken
9.plot: Douglas contacts Donald to warn him about Victor Krane. Unfortunately, Donald doesn't believe him, and now Leo and Tasha are kidnapped.

10.title: Three Minus Bree
10.plot: When Bree is accepted for a high school semester abroad program and Davenport won't let her go, she destroys her chip forsaking her bionic abilities.

11.title: Which Father Knows Best
11.plot: Leo seeks out Douglas' help to replace Bree's destroyed chip while Adam and Chase explore ways to replace Bree.

12.title: Cyborg Shark Attack
12.plot: Only aiming to pay Leo back for humiliating him and Adam at school, Chase sets a cyborg shark with artificial intelligence loose in the house.

13.title: You Posted What? Part 1
13.plot: A viral video of Adam, Bree and Chase handling a mission outs their bionic secret, but Leo discerns that the emergency was a set-up just for that purpose.

14.title: You Posted What?! Part 2
14.plot: With Victor Krane at large and the other Davenports held by government agents, Douglas only knows one way to fix Leo's crushed arm - make him bionic.

15.title: Armed & Dangerous
15.plot: Agent Graham takes the bionic teens on a whirlwind press tour, ignoring the need for missions and training, and reducing Donald to an office gopher.

16.title: Alien Gladiators
16.plot: The Davenports attend a fan convention where Adam, Bree and Chase dress as their favorite "Alien Gladiators" characters, and Leo and Doanld compete for a walk-on role.

17.title: Brother Battle
17.plot: Douglas unlocks new abilities for Adam and Chase that escalate their battle of one-upping and disrupt the balance of power on the team.

18.title: Spike Fright
18.plot: When Chase finally gets a girl interested in him, Adam gets jealous and sabotages their date by purposefully causing Chase to turn into Spike.

19.title: Face Off
19.plot: Bree attempts to play a prank on Adam, but it goes awry right before her big date for the school's winter dance.

20.title: Merry Glitchmas
20.plot: Tasha snags some toys from the lab for her Christmas toy drive, not knowing Chase empowered them with bionics.

21.title: Rise of the Secret Soldiers: Part 1
21.plot: As Adam, Bree and Chase become celebrities, their friction becomes evident when a reality show follows them on a mission and things go awry.

22.title: Rise of the Secret Soldiers: Part 2
22.plot: With the bionic team dissolved, Victor Krane and his bionic army launch a scheme for world-domination.

23.title: Bionic House Party
23.plot: In transferring some of his own life energy to keep Donald from dying, Leo starts aging rapidly. Meanwhile, Krane's teen army, bereft of a leader for the first time, latch on to a new one - Adam.

24.title: First Day of Bionic Academy
24.plot: To his dismay, Leo finds out that he will be a student at the Bionic Academy, not a mentor like Adam, Bree and Chase. Chase engages in a battle against a former nemesis and Adam mentors a younger student.

25.title: Adam Steps Up
25.plot: Donald leaves Adam, Bree and Chase in charge of the Bionic Academy while he celebrates his anniversary. Leo invites Janelle to the island but gets distracted by his nemesis.

26.title: Unauthorized Mission
26.plot: Spin leads Bob on an unauthorized mission while Chase and Sebastian pay Adam back for breaking their training simulator.

imdb.plot outline: When 14-year-old Leo's mom Tasha Dooley marries billionaire inventor Donald Davenport, he moves up in the world, but neither he nor his mom in their wildest dreams imagine that Leo will soon find three bionic super-powered teenagers - Adam, Bree and Chase - living within a secret lab beneath the inventor's expansive home. Now Leo has three older "siblings" to watch out for him while he introduces them to the outside world. School life and super-adventures await them all.

After Tasha Married Donald Davenport, a Multi-Millionare with his own company, she moves in with him and her son. But when her son realizes he actually has 3 bionic kids living in his basement he introduces them to the world ... But can they keep the secret that there bionic?

A young teenager named Leo Dooley lived a normal life until the day his mother Tasha gets remarried to billionaire inventor Donald Davenport, whom they move in with. While trying to find his bedroom, Leo accidentally discovers teenage siblings with bionic powers living in his new basement. The show follows the bionic teens as they unravel in adventurous situations in an attempt to live life like a normal family in the fictional town of Mission Creek, California. As the show progresses in the second, third, and fourth seasons, it gets darker with the introduction of Donald's younger brother Douglas Davenport who later joins the _Lab Rats_ (qv)' side, Douglas' android son, Marcus Davenport, Victor Krane, Taylor (formerly known as S-1), who joins the _Lab Rats_ (qv) during the fourth season, Sebastian (formerly known as S-3), Krane's bionic soldiers, Giselle, who's planning on rebuilding Marcus, and Troy West, Giselle's android creation. At the end of the third season, Donald opens up a bionic academy on a bionic island to train Krane's bionic soldiers to be the world's new bionic heroes.
